Class MyLinkedList2

  • java.lang.Object
    • MyLinkedList2

  • public class MyLinkedList2
extends java.lang.Object
    This is doubly-linked list implementation. Does not implements most of optional list operations, and permits only Integer values (not including null). All of the operations perform as could be expected for a doubly-linked list. Note that this implementation is not synchronized. If multiple threads access a linked list concurrently, and at least one of the threads modifies the list structurally, it must be synchronized externally.

      • divide

        public MyLinkedList2[] divide()
        Returns an array of two lists of the elements in this list. The first list contains all numbers that are multiples of three, the second - all the rest.
        Returns:
        an array of two lists of the elements calculated as above

      • newList

        public MyLinkedList2 newList()
        Returns a new MyLinkedList2 instance with the elements which are calculated as follows: the first element is multiplied with the last one, the second one is multiplied with the penultimate element, and so on. Thus, the returned list contains the same number of elements as in the original list, and each element is repeated twice.
        Returns:
        list of the elements calculated as above
